bot_response: The Gene Set Enrichment Analysis (GSEA) for T cells has identified several significant enrichment terms. Notably, the "Kidney-nk Cell" pathway is highly significant with a p-value of 1.86e-23. Other significant pathways include "Muscle-mature Nk T Cell," "Kidney-cd8-positive, Alpha-Beta T Cell," "Spleen-nk Cell," and "Mammary-nk Cell," each with a p-value of 1.45e-18. In total, 281 terms were found to be significant in the analysis. You can explore these results further through the interactive plots available in the UI.
